Responsibilities

Your role is to develop new concepts and craft world-beating copy that convert traffic into eager and knowledgeable users of our products. You will:

 - Develop a consistent tone of voice for Reedsy across multiple channels;

 - Own and evolve our brand guidelines;

 - Help onboard writers to ensure consistency across every channel;

 - Write copy for our landing pages, lead magnets, email campaigns, newsletters and social media posts;

 - Come up with new creative ideas to convert our traffic;

 - Review copy performance (open rates, click-through, conversions) and use those learnings to sharpen future work;

 - Work closely with a team of content creators (writers, illustrators, animators, and YouTubers) on ad and modal copy, graphic assets, storyboards and video scripts; and

 - Bring a high standard to your own copy and honest, useful feedback to everyone else's.

Person Specification

 - Both a very analytical and highly creative individual;

 - Experience creating conversion copy for large-scale campaigns at a fast-growth startup;

 - A varied portfolio of copy, from short form to long form;

 - Ability to write with range, from playful campaign headlines to technical writing concepts;

 - Proven experience shaping brand guidelines and tone of voice;

 - Familiarity with the publishing industry and writing craft concepts;

 - Experience with email marketing, conversion optimization and A/B testing;

 - Familiarity with Google Analytics and other analytics tools; and

 - Native-level English speaker.

Bonus Points

 - Fluent in multiple languages. Reedsy welcomes applicants of all cultures and backgrounds;

 - A good dose of ambition, a willingness to learn, and a great sense of fun;

 - Your writing has been published in some shape or form.

